d 'HATEMIJ': module to perform Hatemi-J cointegration test with two unknown breaks
d
d   hatemij implements the Hatemi-J (2008) test for cointegration
d with two unknown breaks, computing the three statistics ADF*,
d Zt*, and Za*. Three specifications are supported (level shift,
d level shift with trend, and regime shift), with critical values
d from Hatemi-J (2008) for up to four regressors. Six ADF
d lag-selection rules are available (fixed, AIC, BIC, downward-t
d with a 1.96 or 1.645 cutoff, and a Breusch-Godfrey test based
d selection), together with three long-run-variance kernels (iid,
d Bartlett, Quadratic-Spectral). The cointegrating regression with
d breaks can be estimated by the code. The package was validated
d against Hatemi-J's own Gauss code (coint2b) and the tspdlib Gauss
d library of Saban Nazlioglu. 
d
d KW: cointegration
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260625
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f hatemij.ado
f hatemij.sthlp
